{"title":"Bianchi joins the fast gravel crowd with sleek 2×-friendly Impulso","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/bianchi-impulso-gravel-bike","date":1700673866000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/bianchi-impulso-gravel-bike\">Bianchi joins the fast gravel crowd with sleek 2×-friendly Impulso</a></p>\n\n<p>Bianchi says that aerodynamic performance, low weight, and off-road capability are the hallmarks of the renewed Impulso family, which it’s just launched, aimed at fast gravel riders.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It highlights the growing divide between gravel racers and those looking for slower progress off-road, which it labels adventure cycling, saying that <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/an-introduction-to-bikepacking\" target=\"_blank\">bikepacking </a>and exploration are sub-specialisms. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>As with the latest <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/bianchi-specialissima-rc-2024\" target=\"_blank\">Specialissima </a>and Oltre, there are three spec levels for the new Bianchi Impulso: RC, Pro and Comp. Prices range from €2,459 plus VAT to €5,578 plus VAT.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Designed for a fast spec</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"652\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/513A0542-970x652.jpg\" alt=\"Bianchi Oltre RC\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/513A0542-970x652.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/513A0542-300x202.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/513A0542-768x516.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/513A0542-1536x1032.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/513A0542-2048x1376.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/513A0542-750x504.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/513A0542-1140x766.jpg 1140w\" /><figcaption>Bianchi </figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Impulso RC is the top spec, where Bianchi has aimed for integration and holistic design. It’s aero and Bianchi has engineered a longer reach, pairing it with shorter stem lengths for the one-piece cockpit. Bianchi doesn’t provide extra mounts on the frame, to keep the design light, clean and aero.</p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/unbound-gravel\">‘It’s like Glastonbury for bikes’: Inside the epic Unbound gravel race</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/uci-gravel-world-championships-2022-tech\">UCI Gravel World Championships tech gallery: Variation and improvisation</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/us-gravel-races-dates-routes-tv-enter\">USA gravel races 2023: Race dates, routes, TV coverage, past winners and how to enter</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/best-gravel-bike\">Best of the best gravel bikes 2023: Cyclist’s top-rated gravel and adventure bikes</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article></div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <span></span><span></span><span></span>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        </div>\n\n\n<p>There’s clearance for 42mm tyres – enough for the off-road racer, but a little narrow for the adventure cyclist. There’s also a highish 70mm bottom bracket drop figure to enhance stability. Bianchi says that you can fit a 52/46 Shimano or 48/43 SRAM <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/best-gravel-gearing-how-to-get-lower-gears\" target=\"_blank\">crankset</a>, in line with the fast gravel orientation.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The new Impulso inherits the close integration of the fork and head tube seen on the Oltre and Specialissima, where Bianchi says the new design provides the greatest aero gains. As with those bikes, Bianchi says that it’s concentrated material at the front for stiffness, while the rear of the frame is thinned out for compliance, which is augmented by the D-shaped seatpost.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"650\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/513A0514-970x650.jpg\" alt=\"Bianchi Oltre RC\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/513A0514-970x650.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/513A0514-300x201.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/513A0514-768x515.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/513A0514-1536x1029.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/513A0514-2048x1372.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/513A0514-750x503.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/513A0514-1140x764.jpg 1140w\" /><figcaption>Bianchi </figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Bianchi claims that the 340g one piece carbon cockpit with its 16-degree flared bars is also now stiffer. It allows internal cable routing and is available in nine length/width combinations with widths down to 400mm, following the trend for narrower bars on gravel race bikes, albeit not the extremes of the <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/reviews/bmc-kaius-review\" target=\"_blank\">BMC Kaius’s 36cm bar</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/513A0644-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"Bianchi Impulso RC43 gravel wheelset\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/513A0644-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/513A0644-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/513A0644-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/513A0644-1536x1025.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/513A0644-2048x1366.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/513A0644-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/513A0644-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/513A0644-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/513A0644-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/513A0644-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>Bianchi </figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>There’s a new RC43 aero wheelset to complement the top spec Impulso RC, which has a 43mm deep section and 25mm <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/road-gravel-bike-rim-width\" target=\"_blank\">internal rim width</a> and a claimed 1,570g weight.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Bianchi Impulso range and prices</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"648\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/513A0424-970x648.jpg\" alt=\"Bianchi Impulso RC\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/513A0424-970x648.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/513A0424-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/513A0424-768x513.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/513A0424-1536x1026.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/513A0424-2048x1368.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/513A0424-750x501.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/513A0424-1140x761.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/513A0424-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/513A0424-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/513A0424-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>Bianchi</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Impulso RC is priced at €5,578 plus VAT and comes in a silver celeste colourway. It’s available in five sizes and Bianchi claims an 8.1kg weight.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"642\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/513A0396-970x642.jpg\" alt=\"Bianchi Impulso Pro\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/513A0396-970x642.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/513A0396-300x199.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/513A0396-768x508.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/513A0396-1536x1016.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/513A0396-2048x1355.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/513A0396-750x496.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/513A0396-1140x754.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/513A0396-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>Bianchi </figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Move down the range and the Impulso Pro costs €3,463 plus VAT. It swaps out the RC’s components for wheels and saddle from Bianchi’s Velomann sub-brand and has a two-piece bar and stem. It’s available in celeste or steel grey. Claimed weight is 8.9kg.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"650\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/513A0368-2-970x650.jpg\" alt=\"Bianchi Impulso Comp\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/513A0368-2-970x650.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/513A0368-2-300x201.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/513A0368-2-768x515.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/513A0368-2-1536x1029.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/513A0368-2-2048x1372.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/513A0368-2-750x503.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/513A0368-2-1140x764.jpg 1140w\" /><figcaption>Bianchi </figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Finally, the Comp spec, priced at €2,459 plus VAT, includes Fulcrum alloy wheels and a lower spec Velomann saddle and comes in celeste or gold-brown. Bianchi hasn’t provided a weight figure.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Check out our pick of the <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/best-gravel-bike\" target=\"_blank\">best gravel bikes</a> for more fast gravel options.</em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/bianchi-impulso-gravel-bike\">Bianchi joins the fast gravel crowd with sleek 2×-friendly Impulso</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a>.</p>","author":"pnorman","siteTitle":"Cyclist.co.uk","siteHash":"561486e7070fa5351de9318ad0fa26c2a39332acba5fc7c7d1694a01d53d431e","entryHash":"dad3048d3c8522c449b0fbee501e60473a64188737c98d640f84d3873cab7010","category":"Cycling"}